cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.LG

This paper combines network science, psycholinguistics, and Big Data to analyze textual data and extract relevant concepts. It also focuses on social media perception and online discourse. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Other likely sub-categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
